Jose Wynne has succeeded Jeffrey Young as head of North America foreign-exchange research at
Barclays Plc in  New York , according to a company spokeswoman.  Wynne, 39, has been at Barclays since 2010 and was
previously a director on the firmâ€™s emerging-markets research
team, according to Kristin Friel, a company spokeswoman. He
previously worked at Citigroup Inc.  He will report to London-based  Paul Robinson , head of
global foreign-exchange research, Friel said.  Young, who has left the firm, joined Barclays in October,
according to a company release published at the time. He had
